We're delighted to announce the [Global Voices Citizen Media Summit
2012](https://summit2012.globalvoicesonline.org/)! Our gathering takes place
this year in Nairobi, Kenya on July 2-3, 2012, in partnership with Nairobi's
[iHub](http://ihub.co.ke/pages/home.php "iHub").

Visit the [ Summit web site](https://summit2012.globalvoicesonline.org/) for
background information on [the goals of the
meeting](https://summit2012.globalvoicesonline.org/about/) – we'll be adding
registration details very soon.

![](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/summit-
site-375x281.png)

Over the next days and weeks we'll be fleshing out the program, adding speaker
bios, a list of attendees and more — and do keep checking in at the site for
blog posts and commentary from Summit participants and others, as well as to
join in the conversation.

The Global Voices Citizen Media Summit 2012 has been made possible thanks to
the generous support of [Google](http://www.google.com "Google"),
[Hivos](http://www.hivos.nl/eng "Hivos"), [MacArthur
Foundation](http://www.macfound.org/), the [Open Society
Foundations](http://www.soros.org/), [Adessium
Foundation](http://www.adessium.org/ "Adessium"), [Knight
Foundation](http://www.knightfdn.org/), [Omidyar
Network,](http://www.omidyar.com/) and [Yahoo!](http://www.yahoo.com/).

Current major sponsors include MacArthur Foundation, Google, Open Society
Institute, Knight Foundation and Yahoo!

